<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,284,1846]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,456,1579,1605]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology:</emphasis>
Clifford D. Ferris of Laramie, Wyoming sent me (MGP) specimens that I identified as 
<emphasis box="[420,550,1620,1645]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicName box="[420,546,1620,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Schinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albafascia">albafascia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
After Dr. Ferris insisted that they looked different, I dissected a male and found that there was no hair pencil, which is prominent in 
<emphasis box="[1099,1229,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1225,1660,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Schinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albafascia">albafascia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
We are honored to name this species after Dr. Ferris.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,284,1846]" box="[312,1077,1739,1766]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,482,1739,1765]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Flight period.</emphasis>
This species flies throughout September (
<figureCitation box="[976,1064,1740,1766]" captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="28.[264,368,1064,1088]" captionTargetBox="[291,1307,347,1022]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[271,1315,326,1040]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 45. Flight periods of Schinia species." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168951/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1031,1064,1740,1766]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
